(100, 'Tools used in Sheet Metal Shop', 'The commonly used tools in sheet metal shop are:  A. Hand shears or snips B. Hammers C. Stakes and stake holder D. Cutting tools E. Measuring tools', 'Curved hand shear, cutting tool, Cutting Tools, Cutting Tools in sheet metal shop, Groover, HAMMERS, Hand seamer, HAND SNIPS, Measuring tools in sheet metal shop, Scribers, Semi-circular protector, Stake Holder, Straight hand shear, Types of hammers, Univ', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'Tools used in Sheet Metal Shop', 'tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop', '<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	The commonly used tools in sheet metal shop are:</h2>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	A. Hand shears or snips<br />\r\n	B. Hammers<br />\r\n	C. Stakes and stake holder<br />\r\n	D. Cutting tools<br />\r\n	E. Measuring tools<br />\r\n	F. Miscellaneous hand tools such as chisels, groovers, seamers, rivet sets and hand punches. Some of the important sheet metal tools are described as under.<br />\r\n	<strong>HAND SNIPS</strong><br />\r\n	These are used to cut thin soft metal sheets of 20 gauge or thinner. They are required to size and shape the sheets. They can make straight or circular cuts. Different types of hand shears are:<br />\r\n	(1)&nbsp;<strong>Straight hand shear</strong>: It is used for general purpose cutting, making straight cuts and trimming extra metal.<br />\r\n	(2)&nbsp;<strong>Universal shear</strong>: Its blades are designed for universal cutting straight line or internal and external cutting of contours. It may be of right hand or left hand type, easily identifiable, as the top blade is either on the right of on the left.<br />\r\n	(3)&nbsp;<strong>Curved hand shear</strong>: It is used for cutting circular or irregular curved shapes ranging from 20 to 35 cm.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/33fa4-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop.jpg"><img alt="tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/33fa4-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop.jpg" style="width: 320px; height: 134px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>HAMMERS</strong><br />\r\n	The various types of hammers used in sheet metal work for forming shapes. The uses of different kind of hammers are given as under:</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/e449d-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-1.jpg"><img alt="tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/e449d-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-1.jpg" style="width: 320px; height: 238px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Types of hammers</strong><br />\r\n	(a) Smoothing hammer. Smoothing hammer is used for leveling and smoothing a sheet metal joint.<br />\r\n	(b) Stretching hammer. Stretching hammer is used for stretching sheet.<br />\r\n	(c) Creasing hammer. Creasing hammer is used to close down joint edges of sheets metal part.<br />\r\n	(d) Hollowing hammer. Hollowing hammer is used for hollowing sheet metal part. It is used for generating sharp radius also.<br />\r\n	(e) Riveting hammer. Riveting hammer is used for forming riveted heads.<br />\r\n	(f) Planishing hammer. Planishing hammer is used for removing small marks or indentations from the sheet metal job surface and to smoothens off the finished sheet metal work.<br />\r\n	(g) Soft hammer or Mallets. Mallets used during working with soft metal sheets. They may be of wood, rubber or raw hide. A mallet strikes a blow with the minimum damage to the surface.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/7868e-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-2.jpg"><img alt="tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/7868e-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-2.jpg" style="width: 320px; height: 238px;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Stake Holder</strong><br />\r\n	The stake holder, which is a rectangular cast iron plate that has tapered holes so that the various stakes may fit in and may be used in different positions for tackling the sheet metal job .</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/8da97-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-4.jpg"><img alt="tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/8da97-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-4.jpg" style="width: 320px; height: 68px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Cutting Tools</strong></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	Commonly used cutting tools involve various types of files, chisels, scraper and hacksaws.<br />\r\n	<strong>Measuring Tools</strong><br />\r\n	1. Folding rule. It is used in measuring and laying out on sheets larger work with accuracy of 0.5 mm.<br />\r\n	2. Steel rule. It is useful in measuring and laying out small work on sheets. It can also measure up to accuracy of 0.5 mm.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Some of the other commonly used hand tools are:-</strong><br />\r\n	<strong>Trammel</strong>: a typical trammel and its operations. It is long rod called a beam on which are mounted two sliding heads used to hold scribing points for scribing work on sheets. The points are adjustable .</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/bdefa-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-5.jpg"><img alt="tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/bdefa-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-5.jpg" style="width: 320px; height: 187px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Scribers</strong>: The different kinds of scribers, which are made with its one end pointed sharp for making scribing lines on metal sheets.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/76984-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-9.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/76984-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-9.jpg" style="width: 239px; height: 65px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Groover</strong>: typical groover consists of two folded edges called locks. The two edges are hooked together and locked with a grooving tool called hand groover. These tools come with grooves of various width and vary in size. The groover is used for offsetting an outside grooved seam.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/486b1-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-6.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/486b1-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-6.jpg" style="width: 224px; height: 306px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Hand seamer</strong>&nbsp;: &nbsp;A hand seamer, which is used for bending narrow portions, which are difficult to fold, by other means. It has two adjustable screws, which can be regulated for width of bend.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/9ab9c-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-7.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/9ab9c-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-7.jpg" style="width: 205px; height: 86px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<strong>Semi-circular Protector</strong>&nbsp;: the semicircular protractor is used to for setting bevels, transferring angles and other classes of work on metal sheets.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/37e28-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-8.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/37e28-tools-used-in-sheet-metal-shop-8.jpg" style="width: 302px; height: 320px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-04-30 10:50:22', 0),
(101, 'Recursion in C', 'When a function calls itself within its own body, it is said to be recursive function and technique is called recursion.', 'Difference between Recursion and Iteration, Iteration, Iteration in C, Iteration in C language, Iteration Vs Recursion, Recursion, Recursion and Iteration, Recursion in C, Recursion in C language, Recursion Vs Iteration', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'Recursion in C', 'recursion-in-c', '<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	When a function calls itself within its own body, it is said to be recursive function and technique is called recursion.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	There must be a condition to stop the recursive call or else recursion may last infinitely. Every recursive call must approach to that condition. The number of times a functions calls itself (function makes recursive call) to approach the solution is called&nbsp;<b>depth of recursion.</b></p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<b><a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/74ff3-recursion-in-c.jpg"><img alt="recursion-in-c" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/74ff3-recursion-in-c.jpg" style="width: 211px; height: 298px; float: left;" /></a></b></p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<strong>e.g.&nbsp;</strong>T0 find factorial of function using Recursion in C</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	void main()</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	{</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	int n=5;</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	clrscr();</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	cout&lt;&lt;sum(n);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	cout&lt;&lt;endl&lt;&lt;fact(n);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	getch();</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	}</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	int fact(int n)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // recursive function to find factorial</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	{</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	int f;</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	if(n&lt;=1)</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	return(1);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	else</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	f=n*<b>fact(n-1);&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // recursive call</b></p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	return(f);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	}</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	int sum(int a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // recursive function to find sum of&nbsp; natural numbers up to &lsquo;a&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	{</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	int s;</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	if(a&lt;=1)</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	return(a);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	else</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	s=a+sum(a-1);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	return(s);</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	}</p>\r\n<h2 data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<b>Recursion Vs Iteration</b></h2>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Recursion is calling of a function within its own body. Where as iteration is execution of certain statements again and again. A statement within body of function invokes recursion whereas iteration is controlled by control structure, depending on certain condition. Recursion goes to a depth and returns back (track back) through same path whereas there is no depth for iteration. Recursion invokes a child process because function is called and control is passed to function but in iteration, no function call is made and control remains within same function.</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-05-07 11:28:40', 0),
(102, 'What are sun spots? Explain solar activity?', 'Sun Spots are the shady spots that are available on the visible disk when the pictures of the sun are clicked in the occurrence of white light. The temperature of the shady spots is too much low as compared to the temperature of their surrounding surface.', 'Explain solar activity, solar activity, sun spots, sun spots and solar activity, What are sun spots, What are sun spots? Explain solar activity?, what is solar activity?', 'Gurpreet Singgh', 'What are sun spots? Explain solar activity?', 'what-are-sun-spots-explain-solar-activity', '<h3 data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Sun Spots</h3>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Sun Spots are the shady spots that are available on the visible disk when the pictures of the sun are clicked in the occurrence of white light. The temperature of the shady spots is too much low as compared to the temperature of their surrounding surface. Due to this reason, the shady spots are black in color. The count of these shady spots vary from time to time i.e. it can either be increased or decreased. After a time interval of about 11 yrs, the regular activity of these sun spots takes place and the interval is known as sun spot cycle.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Magnetic field of these sun spots ranges from 2000 to 3000 gauss, which is very high. During the occurrence of this process, neighboring portions of various sun spots gets brighter in color and are known as solar flares. Soon after the generation of these flares, a large number of electrons, protons and alpha particles are emitted. The generation of these particles results in radio and magnetic disturbances over the earth. Solar flares also have an influence on plant growth.</p>\r\n<h3 data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Solar activity</h3>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	&nbsp;It is the activity which relates to all the other activities taking place on the sun. We can also define solar activity as an activity that is performed on the surface of the sun.</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-05-08 01:31:23', 0),
(103, 'History of C Language', '', 'C Language History, History of C language', '', 'History of C Language', 'history-of-c-language', '<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	In 1960, computer languages came into existence, almost each for a specific function peupose eg Cobol was being used for commercial application, Fortran for engineering and scientific applications and so on. Therefore, These was a need for thinking that instead of learning and using so many languages, each for a different purpose, why not use only one language which can program all possible applications there full an international Committee was set up to develop such a language. This committee developed a language called ALGOL 60. ALGOL 60. didn&rsquo;t become popular because it seemed to be abstract and too general. A new language called combined programming language (CPL) was developed in (CAMBRIBGE UNIVERSITY. CPL was an attempt is overcome the drawbacks of ALGOL 60. However, CPL turned out to be so big, having so many features that it was hard to learn and difficult that it was hand to learn and difficult to implement.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	The Basic Combined programming language (BCPL) was developed by martin richard at cambridge university aimed to solve this problem by bringing CPL down to is basic good failures Unfortunately it turned out to be too less powerful and too specific. Around same time a language called &lsquo;BCPL&rsquo; &lsquo;B&rsquo; was written by keu thompson at AT and T bell Labs as further At specification of&nbsp; CPL. But like &lsquo;BCPL&rsquo; &lsquo;B&rsquo; too tuned out is be very specific.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	DENNIS RITCHIE inherited the features of B and BCPL added some of its own and developed &lsquo;C&rsquo;.</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-05-24 10:34:08', 0),
(104, 'Explain Mixing Of Cells?', 'Consider a large no. of cells connected with each other as shown in fig. Let ‘r’ -> internal resistance of each cell ‘ξ’ -> emf of each cell', 'Cells mixing, Mixing of cells, ', 'Simranjot kaur', 'Explain Mixing Of Cells?', 'explain-mixing-of-cells', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Consider a large no. of cells connected with each other as shown in fig.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Let &lsquo;r&rsquo; -&gt; internal resistance of each cell</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">&lsquo;&xi;&rsquo; -&gt; emf of each cell</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">&lsquo;R&rsquo; -&gt; internal resistance</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Total emf of the combination :</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">&xi;</span><sup style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">&rsquo;</sup><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">&nbsp;= n&xi; &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..(1)</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;"><a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/8b71a-mixing-of-cells.jpg"><img alt="mixing-of-cells" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/8b71a-mixing-of-cells.jpg" style="width: 400px; height: 184px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Total internal resistance of the combination</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">r</span><sup style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">&rsquo;</sup><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">&nbsp;= n/m .(r)</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">If I is the total current in the circuit, then I = &xi;</span><sup style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">&rsquo;</sup><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">/r</span><sup style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">&rsquo;</sup><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">+R</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">I = n &xi;/(nr/m+R)</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">I = mn&xi;/(nr+mR)</span></p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-05-31 11:37:09', 0),
(105, 'Basic Data Types in C', 'Data Types is the study of types of data that are already defined in the compiler or that is already recognised / known to the compiler or data that is allowed to be defined by the user', 'C data types, Cpp data types, data types in c, data types used in c', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'Basic Data Types in C', 'basic-data-types-in-c', '<p>\r\n	<span bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">Data Types is the study of types of data that are already defined in the compiler or that is already recognised / known to the compiler or data that is allowed to be defined by the user.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/18133-datatypes.jpg"><img alt="datatypes-in-c" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/18133-datatypes.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 201px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<h2 bitstream="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	Basic data types in c&nbsp; that are already known to C-compiler are :</h2>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	These data types differ in the type of values that can be stores and the range of data that depends on the memory space allocated for them. The memory space occupied by basic data types and their range is give by the table below :</p>\r\n<table bitstream="" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				<p align="center">\r\n					<b>DATA TYPE</b></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				<p align="center" data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="text-align: center;">\r\n					<b>MEMORY SPACE (in bytes)</b></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				<p align="center">\r\n					<b>RANGE</b></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				Signed int</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				2</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				-32768 to +32767</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				unsigned int</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				2</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				0 to 65535</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				long int</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				4</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				-2147483648 to +2147483647`</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				unsigned long int</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				4</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				0 to 4294967295</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				Float</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				4</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				3.4*10<sup>-38</sup>&nbsp;to 3.4*10<sup>38</sup></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="245">\r\n				Double</td>\r\n			<td data-mce-style="text-align: center;" style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px; text-align: center;" valign="top" width="158">\r\n				8</td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="331">\r\n				1.7*10<sup>-308</sup>&nbsp;to 1.7*10<sup>308</sup></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	char data type consist of ASCII character. A character value occupies 1-byte of memory. A char variable can be signed or unsigned which means they have range of &ndash;128 to 127 and 0 to 255 resp.</p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	A character constant is a ASCII character enclosed in single qoutation mark.</p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	int b=&rsquo;Y&rsquo;;</p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	here, &lsquo;Y&rsquo; is a character constant and will be treated as value 89 which is ASCII value of &lsquo;Y&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<b>in C++ Data Types are further divided into categories :</b></p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<b>(i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><b>Built-in (basic) data types&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : int, float, char, long int etc.</b></p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<b>(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><b>use defined data types&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : struct, union, class, enumeration</b></p>\r\n<p bitstream="" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<b>(iii)&nbsp;</b><b>derived data types&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : array, function, pointer, reference</b></p>\r\n<h2 bitstream="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	&nbsp;Format Specifiers</h2>\r\n<table bitstream="" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" font-size:="" line-height:="" new="" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, " times="">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%d</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Int</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%ld</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Long int</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%u</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>unsigned int</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%lu</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>unsigned long int</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%f</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Float</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%lf</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Double</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%Lf</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Long double</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%c</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>Char</b></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="98">\r\n				<b>%s</b></td>\r\n			<td style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 8px;" valign="top" width="637">\r\n				<b>String</b><br />\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-06-15 09:49:10', 0);
