(106, 'Weight Based Shipping in open cart', 'Steps to setup Weight Based Shipping  First add the Geographical area for which you want to setup weight based shipping.', 'Weight Based Shipping in open cart, Open cart weight based shipping', 'Gurpreet SIngh', 'Weight Based Shipping in open cart', 'weight-based-shipping-in-open-cart', '<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong>Steps to setup Weight Based Shipping</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	First add the Geographical area for which you want to setup weight based shipping.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/e2f05-weight-based-shipping.jpg"><img alt="weight-based-shipping-in-open-cart" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/e2f05-weight-based-shipping.jpg" style="width: 441px; height: 443px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/ecfa0-weight-based-shipping-1.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/ecfa0-weight-based-shipping-1.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 176px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	After you have successfully added the geographical area. Then you need to specify the rates for that particular area.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	Click on Delivery option under supplements tab.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/83c57-weight-based-shipping-2.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/83c57-weight-based-shipping-2.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 308px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	After that click on edit button for Delivery according to weight option.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/33598-weight-based-shipping-3.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/33598-weight-based-shipping-3.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 147px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	Here you will find your geographical zone which you have entered above.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<a href="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/a5cde-weight-based-shipping-4.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/a5cde-weight-based-shipping-4.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 158px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	Now the important thing that how to specify weights for particular quantity. Suppose if you want to specify that for 10 items the rate should be $23. Now till 10 items the rate will be 23 dollars. If the user enters 12. Then he/she will be charged the next higher range i.e. $44. If he will enter 25. Then he will be charged 76 dollars. If any higher range is not mentioned then after 30 he will always be charged 76 dollars for any no of products greater than 30. Other higher ranges can be extended by comma separator between as shown below</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:1.25in;">\r\n	<strong>10:23.00, 15:44.00, 30:76.00</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	After adding rates change the status to included and save.</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.75in;">\r\n	<strong>All Done&hellip;.Cheers&hellip;..</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-06-16 10:05:19', 0),
(107, 'Explain Stellar evolution?', 'Stellar evolution concerns with the life cycle of a star. It states that stars live their lives for several years and at last they are dead. Stars complete their whole life span in the universe.', 'Stellar evolution, How a star takes birth, How a star reaches death', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'Explain Stellar evolution?', 'explain-stellar-evolution', '<h3 data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Stellar evolution</h3>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Stellar evolution concerns with the life cycle of a star. It states that stars live their lives for several years and at last they are dead. Stars complete their whole life span in the universe.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<em><strong>How a star takes birth:</strong></em>&nbsp;The stars consist of a large empty space between them. This space is occupied by the dust particles and various types of gases. Out of the gases, hydrogen is available in a large amount i.e. 75% of the space is covered by hydrogen and the remaining space is covered by helium and other heavy elements. The question arises here is that</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	How can the dust particles and gases are responsible in giving birth to a star?</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	The answer to this question is that, due to the gravitational force present between the stars, the dust particles and gases are attracted towards each other and come closer to one another. As they come close to each other, the formation of cloud takes place and a cloud is formed. The gravitational force of attraction is increased as the dust particles and gas molecules come closer. The cloud is then converted into a heavy sized weight that shrinks very quickly to become as hard as possible.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	Now you will be thinking that how these dust particles and gases will help in the birth of a star. Due to the influence of the gravitational force of attraction between the stars these dust particles and gases came nearer to each other. When they came nearer to each other a cloud is formed. The cloud becomes denser and denser as the molecules came closer. The gravitational forces of attraction also increases as the particles and gas molecules came near to each other.</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	Due to this process the cloud formed is transformed into a heavy mass which shrinks very rapidly to become as hard as possible. The conversion is possible only if the cloud has a weight of about one thousand solar masses. If there is a continuous shrinking then both the temperature and the pressure will keep on increasing in a rapid manner. On reaching at a specific position the cloud will be divided into smaller parts equal to that of a stellar size. After the division, shrinking of each part will continue to rise. At last, the nuclear fusion reaction occurs when the temperature of the parts reaches to a million degree and at that time the emission of light starts. All the individual parts will then become stars and a cluster of stars will be formed.</p>\r\n<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<em><strong>How a star reaches death:</strong></em>&nbsp;Let us cover the concept of &lsquo;shining of star&rsquo; first. The stars shine due to the occurrence of nuclear fusion reaction. In the process of nuclear fusion, a large quantity of hydrogen is transformed into helium and energy is produced. By using this energy, the stars shine and due to these reactions the quantity of hydrogen is decreased and shrinking of the core begins. On the other side, the outer area of star starts its expansion and the temperature of the surface keeps on decreasing. Due to the fall in temperature, a supergiant star is formed. The supergiant star remains alive for thousands of years. The energy is developed at a rapid speed when the star reaches the stage of a supergiant star. With the formation of surplus amount of energy, the explosion of the star takes place and soon after the explosion the star takes the shape of a supernova. Due to this process the star loses a large amount of mass and results in scattering of the mass. At the end, the stars lose their life and death of the star takes place.</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-06-18 10:58:58', 0),
(108, 'What are the uses of amorphous solids?', ' Some of the points are given below which describes the basic use of these solids:  Rubber is a type of amorphous solid which is basically used to create lots of products which we use in our everyday life.  Like shoes, tyres, rubber bands, timing belts et', 'amorphous solids, uses of amorphous solids', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'What are the uses of amorphous solids?', 'what-are-the-uses-of-amorphous-solids', '<p data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	These solids are very useful to us. These solids are used in our daily life very often. Some of the points are given below which describes the basic use of these solids:</p>\r\n<ol data-mce-style="text-align: justify;" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px; text-align: justify;">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rubber is a type of amorphous solid which is basically used to create lots of products which we use in our everyday life. &nbsp;Like shoes, tyres, rubber bands, timing belts etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Amorphous silica is a very useful product. By using amorphous silica we can easily convert the sunlight into electricity. Silica is used in Photovoltaic cells.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Another important amorphous solids is inorganic glass. These are used in laboratory ware, construction materials etc.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Plastic is also a type of Amorphous solid. So, I think there is no need to expain the use of plastic.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-06-22 06:56:35', 0),
(109, 'New and Delete operators', 'New operator is used to create a memory space for an object. In C, there are special functions like malloc(), calloc, alloc to do this. C++ use new operator to allocate dynamic memory (run-time allocation). It returns the address of new object created. If', '', 'Gurpreet Singh', 'New and Delete operators', 'new-and-delete-operators', '<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<b>new operator</b></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	New operator is used to create a memory space for an object. In C, there are special functions like malloc(), calloc, alloc to do this. C++ use&nbsp;<b>new</b>&nbsp;operator to allocate dynamic memory (run-time allocation). It returns the address of new object created. If space is not successfully allocated it returns ZERO (0).</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	float *ptr;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	int *a;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	ptr=new float(10.675);&nbsp;&nbsp; // ptr will get a address where float number 10.675 will be stored</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	a=new int [10]; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // a will geta address where 10 integers can be stores (i.e. 20 bytes in //continous are available)</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	the memory allocated by new operator cannot be released unless we use&nbsp;<b>delete operator.</b></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	<b>delete operator</b></p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	the&nbsp;<b>delete</b>&nbsp;operator is used to destroy the variable space which has been created using the&nbsp;<b>new</b>&nbsp;operator dynamically. It is similar to function&nbsp;<b>free( )</b>&nbsp;in C. The general syntax of delete operator is</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	delete ptr;</p>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Charter&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">\r\n	delete a;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; // where ptr and a are pointers</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-06-22 10:45:31', 0),
(110, 'Fitting Shop Tools', 'In fitting shop various steps are performed on metals to change their desired shape and size to fit them where ever desired.', 'tools used in fitting shop, fitting shop tools, ', 'Karanbir Singh', 'Fitting Shop Tools', 'fitting-shop-tools', '<p>\r\n	In fitting shop various steps are performed on metals to change their desired shape and size to fit them where ever desired using Fitting Shop Tools.<br />\r\n	Types of metals<br />\r\n	1) Ferrous metals:- contains iron as their essential constituent eg. Steel, cast iron<br />\r\n	2) Non-Ferrous metals: &ndash; does not contain iron as their essential constituent eg. Brass, bronze, aluminum etc.<br />\r\n	Safety Precautions<br />\r\n	The following safety precautions should be taken when using hand tool and equipment&rsquo;s.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Fitting tools&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n	The tools used in fitting shop may be classified into following groups.<br />\r\n	<strong>Measuring:</strong>&nbsp;Steel Rule, Inside Caliper, Outside Caliper and Vernier<br />\r\n	<strong>Holding:</strong>&nbsp;All types of vices<br />\r\n	<strong>Cutting:</strong>&nbsp;Chisel, Hacksaw and Files<br />\r\n	<strong>Stricking:</strong>&nbsp;All types of Hammers<br />\r\n	<strong>Drilling:</strong>&nbsp;Various types of Drills<br />\r\n	<strong>Threading:</strong>&nbsp;Tap and Dies<br />\r\n	<strong>Marking:</strong>&nbsp;Scriber, Divider and Center Punch<br />\r\n	<strong>Fixing:</strong>&nbsp;Spanner, Wrenches, Keys and Screw Driver<br />\r\n	<strong>Checking:</strong>&nbsp;All types of Gauges<br />\r\n	<strong>Steel Rule&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n	It is a cliff straight steel strip having all its faces machined true. It can be used to take readings&nbsp; in both cm as well as inches. It is used to set out dimensions.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Try Square</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is made up of a steel blade fixed at right angle to the edge of cast iron stock. It is used to check right angles, the squareness of surface and also used to draw line at right angle.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="fitting-shop-jobs" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/92cd1-fitting-shop--jobs.jpg" style="width: 286px; height: 120px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Combination Sets</strong><br />\r\n	It is commonly useful tool. It corporate all essential features of triangle, protector, spirit level and<br />\r\n	steel rule.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It consist of four parts,:<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>1. Steel Rule&nbsp;</strong>steel rule other parts slide. They are locked in the groove in the blade.<br />\r\n	<strong>2. Square Head &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>can be used by moving the blade as the try square.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="fitting-shop--jobs" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/6a5d2-fitting-shop--jobs-1.jpg" style="width: 400px; height: 267px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>3. Center Head&nbsp;</strong>center square head can be used to extend a line around a corner, to find the center of round<br />\r\n	piece or to find the center at the end of the shaft.<br />\r\n	<strong>4. Protector Head &nbsp;</strong>protector is used for measuring angle and can be clamped in any direction or position.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Scriber</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It is made of steel and one end is sharp pointed and other end is also sharp but having a bent in it. This tool is used for scribing line on work piece.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="fitting-shop-jobs" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/b2407-fitting-shop-jobs-2.jpg" style="width: 216px; height: 340px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Center Punch &nbsp;</strong>primarily a marking tool used in bench work also known as center punch, this tool is used for making center for turning on lathe machine as well as for centering the holes for drilling.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="fitting-shop-jobs" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/f011f-fitting-shop-jobs-3.jpg" style="width: 333px; height: 268px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Divider</strong><br />\r\n	It is used chiefly for spacing, scribing, circling and laying out work. Distance may be taken or<br />\r\n	transferred from the steel rule to the work piece.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt="-fitting-shop-jobs-4" src="http://iowiki.com/assets/uploads/files/27521-fitting-shop-jobs-4.jpg" style="width: 400px; height: 145px; margin: 20px; float: left;" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', 'Published', 0, 0, '2016-08-20 10:32:53', 0),
